Drop AI-slop phrasing from user-facing messages

Rewrite CLI errors, warnings, and prompts that read like generated
prose rather than tool output: dash- and semicolon-joined clauses,
"successfully" and "Please" filler, redundant hand-holding sentences,
and a "Configuration error:" preamble that anyhow already frames.

Also replace the forbidden unicode ellipses in the kubernetes exec
error messages and the adjacent comment with ASCII.

The aim is terse, docker/git-style output. Behaviour is unchanged;
only the text differs. Tests that asserted on the reworded strings
are updated.
